WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.852 --> 00:00:02.852
<i>Previously on</i> Vikings...

2
00:00:04.655 --> 00:00:07.488
<i>The gods desire you
to have a great future.</i>

3
00:00:07.557 --> 00:00:09.475
Hail. Earl Ragnar!

4
00:00:09.543 --> 00:00:10.992
Hail. Earl Ragnar!

5
00:00:13.714 --> 00:00:16.865
How will we ever be
equal now. my brother?

6
00:00:16.934 --> 00:00:18.199
I am with child again.

7
00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:21.085
I know you're a boy. my son.

8
00:00:21.154 --> 00:00:23.800
<i>We have to leave here. They
will shun us like a bad smell.</i>

9
00:00:23.824 --> 00:00:25.791
No one will force
you to go anywhere.

10
00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:27.542
They wouldn't dare.

11
00:00:27.611 --> 00:00:29.711
I have been a
warrior all my life.

12
00:00:29.780 --> 00:00:31.547
I beg you. Lord.

13
00:00:31.615 --> 00:00:35.016
gift me the chance to
die with honor in battle.

14
00:00:35.085 --> 00:00:36.351
Let's take him with us.

15
00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:37.552
Aye.

16
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:39.621
Are these pagans
not men. like we are?

17
00:00:39.689 --> 00:00:42.023
<i>Do they not bleed
when they are cut?</i>

18
00:00:42.092 --> 00:00:43.703
<i>Let us prepare to
defend ourselves.</i>

19
00:00:43.727 --> 00:00:45.928
They are not welcome
in my kingdom.

20
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:53.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

21
00:02:20.024 --> 00:02:24.393
Make way there! Come
on! Make way! Make way!

22
00:02:54.174 --> 00:02:55.740
Brother!

23
00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:01.546
Brother! Where are you?

24
00:03:03.316 --> 00:03:05.249
Aethelwulf?

25
00:03:07.654 --> 00:03:09.887
Thank God you are come.

26
00:03:11.275 --> 00:03:13.670
What on Earth made
you think I would not. sire?

27
00:03:13.694 --> 00:03:17.829
No. I never doubted
you. but others...

28
00:03:17.897 --> 00:03:21.132
Our own youngest
brother fled to Mercia.

29
00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:23.368
He was always
the runt of the litter.

30
00:03:23.437 --> 00:03:26.582
Our parents should've
drowned him at birth.

31
00:03:26.606 --> 00:03:28.766
Where are the heathens now?

32
00:03:28.792 --> 00:03:30.875
Only one. perhaps two days away.

33
00:03:30.944 --> 00:03:32.688
And your forces are
ready and armed?

34
00:03:32.712 --> 00:03:35.597
Yes. if you are
ready to lead them.

35
00:03:35.665 --> 00:03:37.760
I would regard it
a great honor. sire.

36
00:03:37.784 --> 00:03:40.104
to defend our kingdom
and our homeland.

37
00:03:41.338 --> 00:03:43.215
And there's no man
better. Lord Aethelwulf.

38
00:03:43.239 --> 00:03:46.336
The poets sing your
battle praises in the halls.

39
00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:48.910
That's because I paid them.

40
00:03:48.979 --> 00:03:51.746
If you paid them. they'd
sing your praises too.

41
00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:53.247
That's poets for you.

42
00:03:57.554 --> 00:04:00.888
My Lady. pray. have
you no time for laughter?

43
00:04:02.025 --> 00:04:05.727
No. My Lord
Aethelwulf. only for fear.

44
00:04:30.471 --> 00:04:32.471
How soon will they come?

45
00:04:33.357 --> 00:04:35.540
Soon enough.

46
00:04:35.609 --> 00:04:39.444
I hope so. I can't
wait for Valhalla.

47
00:05:04.871 --> 00:05:07.622
Good day to you. folk.
What is the problem here?

48
00:05:07.691 --> 00:05:09.441
The problem is her.

49
00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:12.143
What has she done?

50
00:05:12.211 --> 00:05:15.764
She has had a child.
the boy in her arms.

51
00:05:15.833 --> 00:05:17.015
What of it?

52
00:05:18.068 --> 00:05:19.901
He's not my child.

53
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:25.874
We tried for many years to
have children but without success.

54
00:05:25.942 --> 00:05:29.244
And then. just over a year ago.
a young man came to the door.

55
00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:32.664
I remember the day.
I was making a loom.

56
00:05:32.732 --> 00:05:35.416
The young man said
his name was Rig.

57
00:05:35.485 --> 00:05:40.605
He gave us some good advice on
our work and stayed at our house.

58
00:05:40.674 --> 00:05:42.874
After three days. he left.

59
00:05:42.943 --> 00:05:46.611
and then nine months
later. she gave birth to a son.

60
00:05:52.669 --> 00:05:54.269
Whose child is it?

61
00:05:55.672 --> 00:05:58.240
I do not know. My Lady.

62
00:05:59.343 --> 00:06:01.743
We were all in the same bed.

63
00:06:01.829 --> 00:06:05.947
I was too scared... You see?
She is not an honest woman.

64
00:06:06.015 --> 00:06:07.849
She had sex with Rig

65
00:06:07.917 --> 00:06:11.085
and could not bring
herself to tell me the truth!

66
00:06:15.425 --> 00:06:17.470
Do you know who this Rig was?

67
00:06:17.494 --> 00:06:20.361
No. he was just a young man.

68
00:06:20.430 --> 00:06:22.447
On the contrary.

69
00:06:22.516 --> 00:06:25.883
We know from our ancient stories

70
00:06:25.952 --> 00:06:29.270
that Rig is another
name for Heimdall.

71
00:06:30.941 --> 00:06:33.341
The god Heimdall? My Lady!

72
00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:36.395
Yes. the god Heimdall!

73
00:06:36.463 --> 00:06:39.814
You are fortunate that he chose
your household to appear in.

74
00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:41.232
That's just a story.

75
00:06:41.285 --> 00:06:43.735
Our whole lives
are just stories.

76
00:06:43.804 --> 00:06:46.721
You should be ashamed
you did not trust your wife.

77
00:06:46.790 --> 00:06:49.541
despite the joy and
comfort she has brought you.

78
00:06:49.610 --> 00:06:53.828
and the fact that a god
chose you of all people to visit.

79
00:06:56.199 --> 00:06:58.432
Do not punish her.

80
00:06:58.501 --> 00:07:02.470
but rejoice with her.
drink wine with her.

81
00:07:02.556 --> 00:07:05.974
and sacrifice one of your
animals to Heimdall the god.

82
00:07:08.078 --> 00:07:14.165
But if I hear you have harmed
this woman or this child.

83
00:07:14.234 --> 00:07:16.751
you will answer for it to me.

84
00:07:43.847 --> 00:07:46.909
It seems they intend
to stay here a while.

85
00:07:46.933 --> 00:07:48.833
I had not expected that.

86
00:07:48.902 --> 00:07:51.335
My Lord. why don't we attack?

87
00:07:51.404 --> 00:07:53.044
They have a strong position.

88
00:07:54.474 --> 00:07:57.603
Perhaps if we can make them
leave their position and attack us.

89
00:07:57.627 --> 00:07:59.588
How could we force
them to do that?

90
00:07:59.612 --> 00:08:02.180
They're scavengers.
little more than beasts.

91
00:08:02.249 --> 00:08:04.249
We must be able
to out-think them.

92
00:08:04.318 --> 00:08:07.335
If we leave it much longer.
they'll be even better dug-in.

93
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:09.749
My Lord. if a wolf comes
into your sheep fold.

94
00:08:09.773 --> 00:08:11.517
you don't try to out-think it.

95
00:08:11.541 --> 00:08:13.720
You go in and
drive it away or kill it!

96
00:08:13.744 --> 00:08:15.543
How dare you argue with me?

97
00:08:15.612 --> 00:08:17.729
Lord Aethelwulf. forgive
us. We only meant...

98
00:08:17.798 --> 00:08:19.664
I know what you meant.

99
00:08:19.733 --> 00:08:21.878
You meant that you're already
greater warriors than I am.

100
00:08:21.902 --> 00:08:23.579
although only yesterday
you were still green

101
00:08:23.603 --> 00:08:25.214
sucking on your
mothers' breasts.

102
00:08:25.238 --> 00:08:27.421
Go do your jobs. Set up camp.

103
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:38.916
You see them up there?

104
00:08:38.985 --> 00:08:41.186
Yes. I can see them.

105
00:08:42.572 --> 00:08:44.822
What're we waiting for?

106
00:08:45.492 --> 00:08:47.725
To see what they'll do.

107
00:08:49.462 --> 00:08:52.664
So you want to hand
them the initiative?

108
00:08:52.732 --> 00:08:57.402
We can't afford to lose half our
men by being stupid and attacking.

109
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:02.623
We wait until the
odds are in our favor.

110
00:09:09.515 --> 00:09:11.466
Ah...

111
00:10:15.248 --> 00:10:18.049
Awake! Awake! Under attack!

112
00:10:20.854 --> 00:10:21.902
Arm yourselves!

113
00:10:21.971 --> 00:10:22.987
Rise! Rise!

114
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:28.526
Throw! Throw!

115
00:10:41.124 --> 00:10:42.740
Odin!

116
00:10:45.845 --> 00:10:49.363
They're on us! Weapons!

117
00:11:04.130 --> 00:11:06.347
My Lord! We're being attacked!

118
00:11:24.735 --> 00:11:26.183
Amen.

119
00:12:00.152 --> 00:12:01.152
Who are you?

120
00:12:03.924 --> 00:12:08.426
I'm Lord Aethelwulf.
brother of King Aelle.

121
00:12:08.494 --> 00:12:12.814
You are the brother of the
King. yet you lead his army?

122
00:12:12.882 --> 00:12:13.882
Hmm.

123
00:12:16.019 --> 00:12:18.285
Does he send you
to fight all his battles?

124
00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:21.256
In the bedroom too?

125
00:12:25.311 --> 00:12:29.296
Ragnar! Come and see!

126
00:12:29.365 --> 00:12:34.168
Their iron is stronger
and better than ours.

127
00:12:34.237 --> 00:12:37.905
And we've captured a
dozen of their horses.

128
00:12:38.941 --> 00:12:41.960
I'm hungry already.

129
00:12:42.028 --> 00:12:43.868
What ails you. my friend?

130
00:12:43.897 --> 00:12:46.297
The gods won't lift my curse.

131
00:12:46.366 --> 00:12:50.301
I am fated to live forever
on this miserable Earth.

132
00:12:59.062 --> 00:13:00.139
Who is this?

133
00:13:00.163 --> 00:13:01.862
This?

134
00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:04.448
This is the King's brother.

135
00:13:06.152 --> 00:13:08.353
What do you say?

136
00:13:08.404 --> 00:13:10.724
Shall we go visit the King?

137
00:13:10.757 --> 00:13:14.408
God help us! My
brother defeated. dead.

138
00:13:15.545 --> 00:13:17.345
God help Northumbria.

139
00:13:17.413 --> 00:13:19.641
Sire. we do not know
if your brother is dead.

140
00:13:19.665 --> 00:13:22.650
But we do know. My
Lord. that he was defeated!

141
00:13:24.921 --> 00:13:28.556
Who are these
barbarians. these savages?

142
00:13:28.624 --> 00:13:31.475
Why have they
come to torment us?

143
00:13:31.528 --> 00:13:34.245
Sire. some learned
and wise men say

144
00:13:34.314 --> 00:13:37.598
that these Northmen
have been sent here by God

145
00:13:37.666 --> 00:13:42.319
to punish our people for their
many sins and transgressions.

146
00:13:42.388 --> 00:13:45.072
That we have departed
from the path of righteousness

147
00:13:45.158 --> 00:13:49.277
that our lord set out. so now he
is holding us to terrible account.

148
00:13:53.116 --> 00:13:54.866
Forgive me. sire.

149
00:13:54.934 --> 00:13:58.819
but what if God has not sent
these Northmen here to plague us?

150
00:14:00.273 --> 00:14:02.073
Then who has. pray?

151
00:14:02.142 --> 00:14:05.354
Could it not. sire. rather
be the work of the devil?

152
00:14:05.378 --> 00:14:10.497
Go on then. My Lord.
What is your advice?

153
00:14:10.566 --> 00:14:14.552
My advice. sire. is that. as we
are facing the forces of Satan.

154
00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:17.254
we must resist
them at all costs.

155
00:14:17.323 --> 00:14:22.310
Even at the cost of all
our lives if necessary.

156
00:14:22.379 --> 00:14:27.465
For evil cannot be accommodated
nor yet ever bargained with.

157
00:14:27.534 --> 00:14:29.266
Aye!

158
00:14:31.338 --> 00:14:34.839
Sire. if I might speak?

159
00:14:34.908 --> 00:14:37.558
I put it to you that it might be

160
00:14:37.627 --> 00:14:40.561
that these pagans have come
here by their own account.

161
00:14:40.630 --> 00:14:44.565
and that they are neither
of God nor the devil.

162
00:14:44.633 --> 00:14:46.800
They are just savage men

163
00:14:46.869 --> 00:14:51.155
more interested in robbery and
plunder than in matters of the spirit.

164
00:14:51.223 --> 00:14:53.235
- Then what is your advice?
- Listen to him.

165
00:14:53.259 --> 00:14:55.893
Sire. since they
have come for gain.

166
00:14:55.962 --> 00:15:00.865
then let us offer them enough
money or whatever else they desire

167
00:15:00.933 --> 00:15:03.629
to Go away and
leave us in peace!

168
00:15:03.653 --> 00:15:07.838
Shame! Shame on
you! Shame on you!

169
00:15:07.907 --> 00:15:13.127
He is right! Why
waste more blood?

170
00:15:13.213 --> 00:15:15.980
Let's pay them off! - Foolish!

171
00:15:16.049 --> 00:15:19.850
My Lords. let me think
on it just a little while.

172
00:15:21.321 --> 00:15:24.088
In the meantime. let it be known

173
00:15:24.157 --> 00:15:27.392
I have sent envoys out
to raise more men to arms

174
00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:29.727
for our use if need be.

175
00:15:30.647 --> 00:15:32.763
Long live the King!

176
00:15:42.525 --> 00:15:47.327
Contend. O Lord. against
those who contend with me.

177
00:15:49.198 --> 00:15:53.067
Fight against those
who fight against me.

178
00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:58.606
Draw the spear and
javelin against my pursuers.

179
00:16:00.410 --> 00:16:04.545
Say to my soul. "I
am your salvation."

180
00:16:07.517 --> 00:16:10.685
Sire. they are here.

181
00:16:57.750 --> 00:17:00.384
Greetings.

182
00:17:00.453 --> 00:17:04.087
King Aelle invites your leader
to meet him in his Villa to talk.

183
00:17:06.276 --> 00:17:07.942
Who is your leader?

184
00:17:13.833 --> 00:17:17.351
The King did not know that
his brother was still alive.

185
00:17:17.420 --> 00:17:20.448
He would like to talk to you
about what he can give you

186
00:17:20.472 --> 00:17:22.923
to set his brother free.

187
00:17:29.516 --> 00:17:32.050
Do you accept the
King's invitation?

188
00:17:39.042 --> 00:17:41.142
Where are you going?

189
00:17:54.273 --> 00:17:58.326
We should attack
while they are weak.

190
00:17:58.411 --> 00:18:00.439
How long will it take them
to raise another army?

191
00:18:00.463 --> 00:18:04.365
"Attack. attack. attack!"
That's all he ever says.

192
00:18:07.219 --> 00:18:08.853
I want to talk to the King.

193
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:10.583
What is there to talk about?

194
00:18:10.607 --> 00:18:14.391
Imagine the treasures the
King keeps in his household.

195
00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:15.909
I want them.

196
00:18:15.978 --> 00:18:20.581
I want to see how he lives.
what manner of men they are.

197
00:18:21.817 --> 00:18:23.050
and I'm hungry.

198
00:18:23.119 --> 00:18:24.519
Listen to me.

199
00:18:24.587 --> 00:18:27.671
if we agree to
walk into his house.

200
00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:29.851
he can kill each
and every one of us.

201
00:18:29.875 --> 00:18:32.976
You forget. we hold
his brother hostage.

202
00:18:35.298 --> 00:18:37.848
Why should he care
about his brother?

203
00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:40.101
Do I not care about mine?

204
00:19:14.303 --> 00:19:16.354
They're coming.

205
00:19:49.805 --> 00:19:52.173
My Lord Eadric.

206
00:20:29.329 --> 00:20:33.247
Sire. this man is
Ragnar Lothbrok.

207
00:20:33.316 --> 00:20:35.349
his brother Rollo.

208
00:20:35.417 --> 00:20:36.984
and their companions.

209
00:20:37.053 --> 00:20:40.036
Yes. Ragnar Lothbrok.

210
00:20:41.991 --> 00:20:44.231
We've heard that name before.

211
00:20:46.545 --> 00:20:49.985
We are pleased you
have decided to talk to us.

212
00:21:02.077 --> 00:21:05.829
Perhaps. sire. you should
invite them to eat first.

213
00:21:07.800 --> 00:21:09.199
Forgive me.

214
00:21:10.168 --> 00:21:13.920
Let us feast together
and then talk.

215
00:21:29.672 --> 00:21:30.954
The King!

216
00:21:38.648 --> 00:21:40.747
Ragnar Lothbrok.

217
00:21:40.816 --> 00:21:45.252
may I present my wife.
Ealswith. and my son. Egbert.

218
00:21:52.445 --> 00:21:53.445
Hello.

219
00:21:58.284 --> 00:21:59.524
Go on now.

220
00:22:25.695 --> 00:22:28.312
We need more.

221
00:22:28.381 --> 00:22:33.850
In the name of the Father. and of
the Son. and of the Holy Spirit. amen.

222
00:22:33.903 --> 00:22:36.586
Amen. Amen.

223
00:23:45.474 --> 00:23:47.073
Shall we talk. King?

224
00:23:53.015 --> 00:23:54.064
Very well.

225
00:23:55.351 --> 00:23:57.084
What do you want

226
00:23:57.152 --> 00:24:01.087
for the safe return of my brother
and for leaving my kingdom?

227
00:24:03.125 --> 00:24:04.674
Is he a priest?

228
00:24:06.829 --> 00:24:08.812
He's a bishop of our church.

229
00:24:08.880 --> 00:24:10.864
a man of God.

230
00:24:10.932 --> 00:24:13.634
I too have a man of God at home.

231
00:24:17.340 --> 00:24:20.307
Two thousand pounds
in gold and silver.

232
00:24:20.376 --> 00:24:21.725
What did he say?

233
00:24:21.794 --> 00:24:23.443
How much?

234
00:24:23.512 --> 00:24:25.279
Two thousand pounds.

235
00:24:27.933 --> 00:24:31.334
I do not think I heard you
properly. Ragnar Lothbrok.

236
00:24:31.403 --> 00:24:32.403
Hmm.

237
00:24:36.341 --> 00:24:39.910
Two thousand pounds in weight.

238
00:24:42.464 --> 00:24:44.131
That is the price.

239
00:25:07.105 --> 00:25:09.072
I agree to the terms.

240
00:25:11.109 --> 00:25:12.209
Good.

241
00:25:20.619 --> 00:25:25.605
But first. you must
return my brother.

242
00:25:25.691 --> 00:25:30.527
When we receive payment.
you shall have your brother.

243
00:25:30.596 --> 00:25:34.231
You must give me time to
collect such a vast amount.

244
00:25:37.737 --> 00:25:39.286
And in the meantime.

245
00:25:39.354 --> 00:25:42.506
you and your men must
remain in your camp

246
00:25:42.574 --> 00:25:46.943
and make no further attacks
on my people or their property.

247
00:25:48.614 --> 00:25:50.113
Agreed.

248
00:25:50.182 --> 00:25:53.050
Sire! How can we trust
the word of a pagan?

249
00:25:55.804 --> 00:25:58.204
Let me baptize one of them.

250
00:25:59.491 --> 00:26:02.392
There is one further condition.

251
00:26:02.461 --> 00:26:05.662
I desire that either you
or one of your companions

252
00:26:05.731 --> 00:26:09.233
agrees to be
baptized into our faith.

253
00:26:09.301 --> 00:26:13.303
That way. I can make peace
with a friend and fellow Christian.

254
00:26:13.372 --> 00:26:15.272
and not an enemy.

255
00:26:15.341 --> 00:26:19.576
You want one of us to
become Christian? Yes.

256
00:26:31.857 --> 00:26:33.040
Tostig!

257
00:26:46.722 --> 00:26:50.423
I will be Christian.

258
00:27:11.430 --> 00:27:12.607
My Lady Lagertha.

259
00:27:12.631 --> 00:27:14.176
I hope you can
find it in your heart

260
00:27:14.200 --> 00:27:16.560
to speak to the
wife of the late Earl.

261
00:27:16.602 --> 00:27:19.936
Of course. Hello. Siggy.
Please sit down and join us.

262
00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:24.157
Wait! Earl Haraldson
tried to kill my father.

263
00:27:26.729 --> 00:27:30.530
I know. And if he had succeeded.

264
00:27:30.599 --> 00:27:33.500
I would be standing
where Siggy's standing now.

265
00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:38.338
So what would you
like me to say to her?

266
00:27:42.644 --> 00:27:45.612
I would ask her to sit down.

267
00:27:46.982 --> 00:27:48.314
Thank you.

268
00:27:57.909 --> 00:27:59.676
What can I do for you?

269
00:27:59.745 --> 00:28:02.026
It is what I can do for you.

270
00:28:03.916 --> 00:28:05.398
I want to serve you.

271
00:28:08.970 --> 00:28:11.021
That is not necessary.

272
00:28:16.979 --> 00:28:20.413
I remember very well how I
served the father of my church.

273
00:28:21.149 --> 00:28:22.949
and it did me no harm.

274
00:28:23.018 --> 00:28:27.771
In fact. I found in service
a great freedom and honor.

275
00:28:27.840 --> 00:28:30.435
When I accepted that I
should forget about myself

276
00:28:30.459 --> 00:28:32.626
and serve Father Cuthbert.

277
00:28:33.729 --> 00:28:37.113
well. then I became happy.

278
00:28:52.497 --> 00:28:56.233
If it's really what you
want. I accept your offer.

279
00:28:59.354 --> 00:29:01.021
Thank you.

280
00:29:02.341 --> 00:29:05.241
You and your daughter
are now under my protection.

281
00:29:05.310 --> 00:29:08.161
but I will never treat
you as a servant.

282
00:29:22.777 --> 00:29:27.047
O Lord. Holy Father.
almighty and eternal God.

283
00:29:27.115 --> 00:29:31.135
expel the devil and
his kin from this person.

284
00:29:31.203 --> 00:29:35.605
from the head. from the hair.
from the brain. from the brow.

285
00:29:35.658 --> 00:29:37.507
from the ears.
from the nostrils.

286
00:29:37.576 --> 00:29:40.677
from the mouth. from
beneath the tongue.

287
00:29:40.745 --> 00:29:42.629
from the throat. from the neck.

288
00:29:42.698 --> 00:29:44.459
from the chest. from the heart.

289
00:29:44.483 --> 00:29:47.683
from the entire
interior of the body.

290
00:29:47.752 --> 00:29:51.371
from the thoughts. from the
words. and from the deeds.

291
00:29:51.439 --> 00:29:54.424
in the name of
Jesus Christ our Lord.

292
00:29:55.377 --> 00:29:56.627
Amen.

293
00:29:58.296 --> 00:29:59.713
I anoint thee

294
00:30:02.484 --> 00:30:07.954
in the name of the Father and
of the Son and of the Holy Spirit.

295
00:30:08.757 --> 00:30:10.023
Amen.

296
00:30:22.071 --> 00:30:25.572
I now pronounce you
baptized and born again

297
00:30:25.657 --> 00:30:28.942
with the new
Christian name of Rolf.

298
00:30:40.072 --> 00:30:42.222
May the Lord bless
you and keep you

299
00:30:42.291 --> 00:30:44.424
from this day hence and forever.

300
00:30:44.493 --> 00:30:45.575
Amen.

301
00:31:05.930 --> 00:31:09.599
We have witnessed
a true miracle.

302
00:31:09.668 --> 00:31:13.587
Now I ask you to
fulfill your promises.

303
00:31:13.656 --> 00:31:18.107
Return to your ships and
await your payment in peace.

304
00:31:18.176 --> 00:31:20.193
Agreed. Ragnar Lothbrok?

305
00:31:53.061 --> 00:31:54.611
What is it?

306
00:31:54.679 --> 00:31:56.129
I can't sleep.

307
00:31:59.468 --> 00:32:01.785
Come here beside me. daughter.

308
00:32:11.613 --> 00:32:13.213
What worries you?

309
00:32:13.281 --> 00:32:16.966
I fear for father so far away.

310
00:32:22.640 --> 00:32:27.310
Our lives are fated. Gyda.
We all have to accept that.

311
00:32:33.752 --> 00:32:37.053
I can feel it moving
underneath my hand.

312
00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:40.857
Mmm-hmm. He has a strong kick.

313
00:32:40.925 --> 00:32:43.593
He? Are you so sure it's a boy?

314
00:32:45.664 --> 00:32:48.431
A long time ago.
the Seer prophesized

315
00:32:48.500 --> 00:32:51.201
that your father
would have many sons.

316
00:32:51.270 --> 00:32:53.353
That's how I know it's a boy.

317
00:33:00.929 --> 00:33:02.462
Now sleep.

318
00:33:27.172 --> 00:33:28.788
I won again.

319
00:33:30.275 --> 00:33:33.359
Well done. Rolf.

320
00:33:34.947 --> 00:33:37.075
What's wrong with you. Floki?

321
00:33:37.099 --> 00:33:39.549
There's nothing wrong with me.

322
00:33:39.601 --> 00:33:42.786
I did not renounce the
gods in front of everyone.

323
00:33:44.539 --> 00:33:47.140
It was a joke.

324
00:33:47.208 --> 00:33:49.159
I didn't believe it.

325
00:33:49.228 --> 00:33:52.044
I didn't even know what
the old fool was saying.

326
00:33:52.113 --> 00:33:56.817
It doesn't matter. Surely.
you've made them very angry.

327
00:34:03.258 --> 00:34:05.124
Don't be stupid.

328
00:34:05.193 --> 00:34:10.663
No. you are the stupid one
to risk the wrath of the gods.

329
00:34:10.732 --> 00:34:13.750
How will you ever get
Odin to forgive you now?

330
00:34:16.971 --> 00:34:19.306
They're here! Come and see!

331
00:35:13.362 --> 00:35:14.877
They're empty.

332
00:36:16.924 --> 00:36:18.291
Move back!

333
00:36:18.877 --> 00:36:19.877
Reform!

334
00:36:22.864 --> 00:36:24.047
My men!

335
00:36:24.099 --> 00:36:25.231
Regroup!

336
00:37:25.109 --> 00:37:27.059
Odin!

337
00:38:23.835 --> 00:38:26.535
Valhalla.

338
00:39:29.417 --> 00:39:32.552
How many Christians
did I kill. Floki?

339
00:39:34.088 --> 00:39:35.572
How many?

340
00:39:37.592 --> 00:39:41.410
Do you think Odin is
still angry with me now?

341
00:40:01.483 --> 00:40:02.563
Whoo!

342
00:40:07.539 --> 00:40:11.840
It seems your brother. the King.

343
00:40:11.909 --> 00:40:14.389
does not care
if you live or die.

344
00:40:16.581 --> 00:40:20.750
If you let me talk to him. I will
persuade him to honor his pledge.

345
00:40:36.985 --> 00:40:40.820
Why should I not
just kill you now?

346
00:40:43.158 --> 00:40:46.008
Then you'll have nothing
left to bargain with.

347
00:40:49.263 --> 00:40:51.163
I have this.

348
00:41:06.981 --> 00:41:09.015
Open!

349
00:41:09.084 --> 00:41:11.167
Open the gate!

350
00:42:56.157 --> 00:42:59.158
I swear before God almighty.

351
00:42:59.226 --> 00:43:04.897
I declare war eternal on the
Northman Ragnar Lothbrok.

352
00:43:04.966 --> 00:43:10.319
I swear to our Lord Jesus
Christ and to the Blessed Virgin.

353
00:43:10.388 --> 00:43:15.391
one day. I will
avenge myself on him

354
00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:19.062
and bring him to
justice and to death.

355
00:43:19.130 --> 00:43:21.030
so help me God.

355
00:43:22.305 --> 00:44:22.883
